						<summary>

						<p>Slab lying in survey No. 71, about 1/4 km South of the railway line.</p>						

						<p>This undated inscription may be assigned to the 9th century, on the basis of palaeography.</p>						

						<p>Mutilated. It registers a gift of 30 <hi rend="italic">maṟutus</hi> of land as <hi rend="italic">pannasa</hi> by the queen of Pṛithvīpati.</p>						

						</summary>
